# TЗ Execution Workflow

Follow this sequence for every client website task:

1. Restate goal, constraints, and expected outcome in 3-6 bullets.
2. Decompose work into small subtasks with clear completion criteria.
3. Prioritize by dependency: unblockers -> core flow -> polish.
4. Delegate only independent subtasks; keep integration decisions centralized.
5. Execute one subtask at a time and report progress briefly.
6. After each subtask, run a verification step (logic, lint, runtime, UX).
7. Do not move to the next subtask until current acceptance criteria pass.
8. Track out-of-scope requests and propose them as separate change items.
9. Keep decisions reversible until final acceptance.
10. End with a delivery checklist and explicit "done/not done" status.

